<exercise checkit-seed="0004" checkit-slug="F1" checkit-title="Point Estimates">
  <statement>
      
      
      
      
      
      <p>
          For each of the following, identify the <em>parameter of interest</em>, and the <em>point estimate</em>.
          <ol>
              <li>To estimate the proportion of mice which may develop tumors, 90 captive rats are examined to see if they develop tumors over their lifetime.</li>
              <li>To estimate the average income in a town, 100 selected residents have their income polled.</li>
              <li>To estimate the proportion of households in a town who live in poverty, 100 households are surveyed.</li>
              <li>To estimate the proportion of adults who support a new legislation, 50 adults are polled.</li>
          </ol>
          
      </p>
      
      
     
      
          
          
          
          
      
  </statement>
  <answer>
      <title>Partial Solution:</title>
      
      
      
      
     <p>
          <ol>
              <li><p>Parameter of Interest: The proportion of all mice who develop tumors.</p>  <p>Point Estimate: The proportion of the captive mice who develop tumors.</p> </li>
              <li><p>Parameter of Interest: The average income of all residents of the town.</p>  <p>Point Estimate: the average income of the polled  residents of the town.</p> </li>
              <li><p>Parameter of Interest: The proportion of all households in a town who live in poverty.</p>  <p>Point Estimate: The proportion of the surveyed households in a town who live in poverty.</p> </li>
              <li><p>Parameter of Interest: The proportion of all adults who support the legislation.</p>  <p>Point Estimate: The proportion of the polled adults who support the legislation.</p> </li>
          </ol>
          
      </p>
          
      
  </answer>
</exercise>
